# 2p_rmb_hitscan — client. Same setup as the host: Pulse Rifle primary,
# Sidearm secondary. RMB-fires the Sidearm and expects to see the
# tracer on its own screen (the bug the user reported: client RMB
# Sidearm shows projectiles on server side but NOT on client side).
#
# Assertion target on the client log:
#   `client_fire_event hitscan shooter=N self=1 active=0`
# self=1 + active=0 means "this is my own RMB-on-inactive shot, predict
# didn't draw it, FIRE_EVENT must — and now does".

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/2p_rmb_hitscan_client
network connect 127.0.0.1:24108
name ClientB

loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Sidearm" Light Standard

spawn_at 2540 984
aim 2240 956

at 130 shot t130_pre_match

# Host RMB fires at 140 → client sees HostA's tracer come in.
at 155 shot t155_host_tracer_incoming

# T=200-208: client RMB-fires Sidearm. The pre-fix bug made this
# invisible on the firer's own screen. Post-fix, both the local
# tracer AND the host-side tracer should render.
at 200 press fire_secondary
at 208 release fire_secondary
at 215 shot t215_client_sidearm_rmb

at 280 end
